# Internal OTA (personal phone)

When the user says **push to internal**, **push internal**, **OTA internal**, or similar — publish an **EAS Update** to the personal ad hoc build. Do **not** run a TestFlight / production / store build unless they explicitly ask.

## What “internal” is

| Track | Profile | Channel | Who |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Personal testing | `internal` (ad hoc install page) | `internal` | Avi’s registered iPhone |
| Public beta | `production` (store) | `production` | TestFlight |

- Project: `@avitaub/dispatcher`
- Runtime: `appVersion` policy (`1.0.0` until native version bumps)
- Registered device already on the ad hoc profile — OTA reaches that phone after install of an `internal` binary
- JS/UI-only changes → **update only**. Native module / app.json native changes → `npm run build:internal` (new binary), then updates again

## Command (do this)

```bash
npm run update:internal -- --message "<short what changed>"
```

That runs `eas update --channel internal --environment preview` and texts the update link to Telegram.

Confirm success in the reply (group ID / URL if printed). Do not submit to App Store Connect. Do not use channel `production` or `preview` for this phrase.
